io.janusproject.kernel.repository

Class MultipleAddressParticipantRepository<ADDRESS extends Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.janusproject.kernel.repository.ParticipantRepository<ADDRESS>
      • io.janusproject.kernel.repository.MultipleAddressParticipantRepository<ADDRESS>
  • Type Parameters:
    ADDRESS - - the generic type representing the address of a participant in the related space. This type must remains small, less than M in memory and must be Serializable

    public final class MultipleAddressParticipantRepository<ADDRESS extends Serializable>
extends ParticipantRepository<ADDRESS>
    Repository that maps participants to multiple addresses.

    This repository links the id of an entity to its various addresses in the related space.

    The repository must be distributed and synchronized all over the network by using data-structures that are provided by an injected DistributedDataStructureService.
